text:
As far as I can remember, I always liked to create things, especially on a computer or anything digital. i started to write books online at a very young age and seeing people enjoy my writing gave me more motivation to learn more.That's how I learned to edit videos and photos by myself to give something more to my writings. I wanted to be an author, but as I grew up I decided to be a lawyer, then to work in tourism and then to go for communication. In all those fields i wanted to be in touch with people and digital communication is today the best choice to do so. By working in this field, I can do what I like : create things online and also get "sale" something to people. I really want to work in the digital field because this is a field that is needed today, even more after the covid crisis. Company ha to adapt themself to keep selling products and that's when we saw how important digital communication is important today. Even before that I liked everything that had to do with digital or new technology.I like to code, to learn about new technology products etc.
This is also an "easy" field for me. I have always been more comfortable to write things rather than speak. I like to be behind a computer where no one see me except when they look at my work.
I was also inspired by a lot of women, seeing how they were happy and free in their job pushed me to find something that will also light me up like that and right now nothing does it like digital communication. I always find a way to do digital communication, and this year i do it by working with Com'on in their visual team and in the communication team of the association Prologin. Those two things are just provng to me how much I like to create things and see those things being used to promote something online. I like to tell to myself that maybe because of my work someone bought or did something they wouldn't have normally. This is oddly satisfying to me.
And that is why I want to work in the communication field. I want to be the link beetwen a community/client and the company.
 This webpage perfoms keylogging of input typed into a texbok. In other words, when focused on the texbok below, the page will record each time you hit a key or select text with your mouse. All of the data is stored locally on you machine in the DOM and is downloaded as a JSON file. More information about the motivation of this project and the format of the produced data are available here.
